<quantity box="[590,708,1790,1815]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="262" pageNumber="263" unit="m" value="98.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="46.0">46–150 m</quantity>
). The 
<collectingCountry box="[780,873,1791,1815]" name="Curaçao" pageId="262" pageNumber="263">Curaçao</collectingCountry>
specimen (from 
<quantity box="[1066,1127,1790,1815]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="262" pageNumber="263" unit="m" value="46.0">46 m</quantity>
), an empty shell, may have been transported to a relatively shallow depth by offshore fishermen emptying their gear (bathyal depths occur within a few kilometers of its northern coast). Nonetheless the find places the species in the proximity of the island.
</paragraph>
